translation":"A remembered story name"}],"order":1,"title":"A Story Bite","mechanic":"story_bite","readiness":"placeholder","description":"Hear a tiny story moment and notice one word.","isStartable":false},{"id":"culture-card-drum","items":[{"id":"drum-card","word":"Engoma","order":1,"imageKey":"drum.png","mechanic":"cultural_card","translation":"Drum"}],"order":2,"title":"Culture Card","mechanic":"cultural_card","readiness":"placeholder","description":"Open a small culture card with one familiar object.","isStartable":false},{"id":"story-check-1","items":[{"id":"story-question","word":"Laba ekifaananyi","order":1,"imageKey":"culture.jpg","mechanic":"mini_quiz","translation":"Look at the picture"}],"order":3,"title":"Story Check","mechanic":"mini_quiz","readiness":"placeholder","description":"Answer a gentle question after a story bite.","isStartable":false}],"imageKey":"culture.jpg","isLocked":false,"mechanics":["story_bite","cultural_card","mini_quiz"],"readiness":"placeholder","isPractice":false,"description":"Explore short story moments and cultural cards.","lessonCount":3,"stageNumber":4,"learningGoals":["Hear a short story moment","Learn one cultural idea at a time","Answer a gentle story question"],"estimatedMinutes":5,"placeholderMessage":"Culture & Stories lessons are being shaped. Short story bites and culture cards will open here soon."},{"id":"practice-mix","order":5,"title":"Practice Mix","status":"locked","lessons":[{"id":"review-first-words","items":[{"id":"first-words-review","word":"Webale","order":1,"imageKey":"learning-beginner.jpg","mechanic":"practice_mix","translation":"Thank you"}],"order":1,"title":"First Words Review","mechanic":"practice_mix","readiness":"placeholder","description":"Review words after enough lessons are complete.","isStartable":false}],"imageKey":"african-patterns.png","isLocked":true,"mechanics":["practice_mix"],"readiness":"placeholder","isPractice":true,"description":"Review words after a few lessons are complete.","lessonCount":1,"stageNumber":5,"learningGoals":["Review words from finished stages","Practice words that need another try","Come back to words over time"],"estimatedMinutes":5,"placeholderMessage":"Practice Mix will unlock after enough lessons are completed in the future."}],"localName":"Oluganda","pathTitle":"Luganda Learning Path","displayName":"Luganda","languageCode":"lg"}', 25, true, '2026-07-14 21:34:23.334371+00', '2026-07-15 03:38:59.097031+00', 'published', true, 3, '2026-07-14 18:23:26+00'), ('a9844348-14f8-4a26-b427-62244b129c2c', 'lg', 'child_menu', 'games', 'Games', '{"cards":[{"id":"words","image":"african-focus.png","order":1,"title":"Words","targetPage":"child/games/wordgame","description":"Fill in the missing letters to complete the word"},{"id":"logic","image":"african-logic.png","order":2,"title":"Logic","targetPage":"child/games/puzzlegame","description":"Solve puzzles inspired by popular Buganda heritage sites"},{"id":"cards","image":"cards-matching.png","order":3,"title":"Cards Matching","targetPage":"child/games/cardgame","description":"Match the cards to learn about Buganda cultural items"},{"id":"learning","image":"african-patterns.png","order":4,"title":"Learning","targetPage":"child/games/learninggame","description":"Learn common Luganda words and how they are used in sentences"},{"id":"numbers","image":"numbers.png","order":5,"title":"Numbers","targetPage":"child/games/lugandacountinggame","description":"Count with Luganda number labels"}]}', 10, true, '2026-06-19 07:58:49.994863+00', '2026-07-14 21:34:32.860724+00', 'published', true, 1, '2026-07-14 18:23:26+00'), ('baf75b1a-368f-4282-a221-c454e78fd29a', 'lg', 'story', 'mwanga', 'Kabaka Mwanga II', '{"id":"mwanga","pages":[{"id":"mwanga-page-1","text":"Kabaka Mwanga II became the king of Buganda in 1884 when he was very young. He inherited a kingdom that was changing rapidly as Europeans brought new ideas and religions.","image":"story/mwanga/mwanga1.jpg","altText":"Young Kabaka Mwanga II being crowned as king"},{"id":"mwanga-page-2","text":"At first, Mwanga allowed Christian missionaries to teach in his kingdom. Many Baganda people, including royal pages who served in the king''s court, began to follow these new religions.","image":"story/mwanga/mwanga2.jpg","altText":"Missionaries teaching Baganda people at the royal court"},{"id":"mwanga-page-3","text":"However, Mwanga became worried that his people''s loyalty was shifting away from him and Buganda traditions. The new Christians were refusing to follow some of the king''s orders.","image":"story/mwanga/mwanga3.jpg","altText":"Kabaka Mwanga looking concerned as people gather around missionaries"},{"id":"mwanga-page-4","text":"In 1885, Mwanga ordered the execution of three missionary teachers. Later, he commanded that many converted Baganda Christians be put to death at Namugongo for their disobedience.","image":"story/mwanga/mwanga4.jpg","altText":"A solemn scene representing the martyrs of Namugongo"},{"id":"mwanga-page-5","text":"These people became known as the Uganda Martyrs. Their bravery inspired even more Baganda people to become Christians, which was the opposite of what Mwanga had intended.","image":"story/mwanga/mwanga5.jpg","altText":"People gathering to honor the memory of the martyrs"},{"id":"mwanga-page-6","text":"As European influence grew, Mwanga faced many challenges to his rule. In 1888, he was overthrown but fought to regain his throne. Later, he resisted British colonial control.","image":"story/mwanga/mwanga6.jpg","altText":"Mwanga leading resistance against colonial forces"},{"id":"mwanga-page-7","text":"In 1899, Mwanga was captured by the British and exiled to the Seychelles Islands, far from his homeland. He never returned to Buganda and died in exile in 1903.","image":"story/mwanga/mwanga7.jpg","altText":"Mwanga being taken away on a ship to exile"},{"id":"mwanga-page-8","text":"Today, Kabaka Mwanga is remembered as a complex figure in Buganda''s history—a king who fought to preserve his kingdom''s independence during a time of great change and outside influence.","image":"story/mwanga/mwanga8.jpg","altText":"A memorial to Kabaka Mwanga with both traditional and modern elements"}],"title":"Kabaka Mwanga II","summary":"Discover the story of Kabaka Mwanga II of Buganda","metadata":{"notes":"Migrated from legacy hardcoded Luganda story components into content_items-compatible story payloads.","status":"existing-prototype"},"questions":[{"id":"mwanga-question-1","options":["1776","1825","1884","1901"],"question":"When did Kabaka Mwanga II become king of Buganda?","correctAnswer":2},{"id":"mwanga-question-2","options":["They were teaching people to read","People''s loyalty was shifting away from him and traditions","They were building too many churches","They wanted his crown"],"question":"What worried Mwanga about the Christian missionaries?","correctAnswer":1},{"id":"mwanga-question-3","options":["A new palace was built","Converted Baganda Christians were executed","Mwanga was crowned","Europeans established a trading post"],"question":"What happened at Namugongo?","correctAnswer":1},{"id":"mwanga-question-4","options":["Christianity disappeared from Buganda","Even more Baganda people became Christians","Mwanga became more powerful","The missionaries left Uganda"],"question":"What effect did the martyrs'' deaths have?","correctAnswer":1},{"id":"mwanga-question-5","options":["He was captured by the British and exiled","He defeated the British forces","He converted to Christianity","He united all Ugandan kingdoms"],"question":"What happened to Kabaka Mwanga in 1899?","correctAnswer":0}],"languageCode":"lg"}', 61, true, '2026-07-01 09:45:23.564353+00', '2026-07-14 21:34:32.860724+00', 'published', true, 1, '2026-07-14 18:23:26+00'), ('bb96c3b2-3199-4f4a-b2a0-25b2c0c2384c', 'lg', 'learning_game', 'starter', 'Luganda Learning', '{"stages":[{"id":1,"color":"#4F85E6","image":"coin.png","order":1,"title":"Beginner","levels":[{"id":1,"order":1,"ti